The chair of the founder and first great general of Cipher.  Destructive Dirk, the original Asmodeus.  There was rumour of an attempted overthrow at one point, but the great leader quelled the rebellion.  He has stepped down from his leadership duties now, and seeks the fabled "Tenth Circle" - a plane of existence so terrible, none of the other Lord's of the Nine have dared to find it.

Welcome to the Cornfield.




The world is changing. Much that once was is now lost for none now live who remember it.... 

History has become legend and legend has become myth. The origin of the CIPHER faction is lost in the mists of time. Only legend and rumor speak of where they come from and who they once were. 

What is known for certain is that such a group once existed in another realm. They grew in power, prestige and arrogance until they dared to oppose the very deities that dwelled in that realm. For the hubris of their leaders the entire faction was struck down wiped of the face of the realm. 

The Gods decreed that the name CIPHER shall never be spoken aloud again. All history books were wiped of any sign that the guild had existed and the leaders of the guild were hurled through a portal to wonder the endless void eternally. The deities decreed that the name CIPHER shall pass from the realms of men and forgotten in the mists of time. 

But even the Gods could not destroy an idea. The CIPHERS should have died and been wiped from memory of men but they lingered still. Something stirred in the darkness. A low hissing whisper was heard in the void. The ETERNAL SERPENT had stirred form the very depths of HELL and whispered in Dirk Blackwood's ear. The gentle yet undeniably evil voice guided the small band of Ciphers through the palpable darkness to a destination unknown. It is here, the voice whispered, that the final battle for the hearts and minds of men would be fought. The evil, yet strangely soothing whispers of the Serpent, guided the small ragged band to a new realm, one filled with danger and conflict..... 


A NEW BEGINNING 

A small ragged band of CIPHERS were unceremoniously dumped on their rear ends in the small town of Loftenwood. As they emerged through the portal, which seemed to be ripped through the fabric of reality by the claws of the serpent, a new and strange land lay before them to be explored and conquered. 

Whereas, before The Grey Council (as the Cipher leadership was known then) had been used to supreme power they were rendered powerless by their arduous journey. Gone were the trappings of their authority and their hordes of magical items as well as their vast store of lore and knowledge. They were alone in a new strange land. 

This small group that was hurled through the portal was no mere group of novice adventurers. It was a group built on war and conquest, a group filled with experienced adventurers whose skills were heralded across the lands. They had fought many wars and had laid waste to many factions on the path to their ascension. They were war generals and warriors of renown. 

It is no wonder then that almost upon their arrival they engaged in a series of battles with the powerful factions who dwelled in the lands. The Grey Council viewed their role as a force of balance then, not a force for evil they would soon become. The ETERNAL SERPENT's whispers in the darkness had not corrupted their hearts yet. But the serpent watched and smiled in the silence as more and more blood was spilled. It was only a matter of time. 

The lands surrounding Loftenwood were besieged by the Dark Legion. Their hordes trampled the cowed populace underfoot. No one dared oppose them untill a last alliance of factions, including the Ciphers steped forth to oppose them. The bloody series of endless wars had begun. The ETERNAL SERPENT watched silently in the Deepest Pit. He, more then anyone else, knew that violence beget violence. Soon his favored warriors would turn to the darkness. 

Battle after bloody battle brought both strength and more conflict. More and more evil hearted warriors were drawn to the CIPHER cause and more and more wars were fought. The decades that passed saw the Cipher faction declare both alliances and wars with Legion, Sole and Order. Through conflict, strife and battle prowess the faction grew and was reborn into a force once again. Yet, they were beset on all sides. Hunted by Legion, persecuted by Order, attacked by Sole as well as facing threats from the numerous new guilds and organizations that had arisen throughout the land. 

The Ciphers called out to that soothing whisepr inthe darkness, the ETERNAL SERPENT who had been waiting patiently on his skull encrusted throne. The time had come to imbue his most prized instruments of destruction with the power to execute his will upon all others. 


THE DARK PACT 

Long had it been known that Ciphers leaders especially the ancient wizard Dirk Blackwood had trafficked with infernal powers in their quest for mastery over all magic. Some attribute his unnatural longevity to his pact with the dark powers. The ancient wizard had walked the lands of men for over 300 years and still lost none of his vigor. 

The time had come to perform the blasphemous ceremony that the Grey Council had discovered from an ancient manuscript placed carefully in their possession by the Serpent's minions. Many sacrifices would be needed. The blood of many innocents had to be spilled. 

The summoning was a ceremony of the utmost power. A black pentagram was first etched with the acid dripping from a fang of an ancient Black Dracolich (Some even claim it was the fangs of Vorthese the undead Dragon). The hollow etchings were then filled with the black ichor from the veins of 66 Balors that dwelled in Blighted City. Then the magical pentagram was imbued with ancient symbols of Summoning and all the knowledge and power of the venerable Grey Council. The final ingredient was the blood of 666 innocents. As the Ciphers went about this grizzly business slaughtering adventurers of all factions and different power their fate became inextricably sealed. As the blood of the last innocent was spilled, their alignment shifted to Infernal Evil. Their souls now belonged to the ETERNAL SERPENT! 

The ceremony was now complete. The Grey Council waited impatiently. With a deafening explosion the coiled Serpent moved its ponderous form from the depths of the Ninth Pit. The sky over Loftenwood darkened. The sun hid, as though in fear, behind the clouds. A plague of insects and toads covered the cities of Ridgetown and Tanglebrook. The river between Duvanbawer and Mythara turned to fetid blood. The land shuddered at the blasphemy that had entered it. The beasts and trees of the land shriveled and fled. Evil had come to the land. 

The mere sight of the unknowable infinite Serpent struck the Grey Council blind and the infernal maelstrom that followed it knocked them prone, stunned and speechless. 

The ETERNAL SERPENT spoke to his followers. His voice was as low as the hiss of a serpent yet loud enough to drown out the roar of an ocean. Its echo reverberated in those dank blood spattered halls, rumored to be the shattered temple. Some say the echo of this infernal blasphemy can be heard in the halls of the Shattered Temple to this very day: 

"Long have I watched your progress my children. You have done well. You have spilled the blood of many innocents. But I require more from you. Your souls are now eternally mine and you shall be rewarded for your service as long as you shall serve me. You have entreated me for power and you shall receive it! You shall now wield the Power of the Lords of the Nine. Each is a devil of utmost power who rules one of the Nine Pits of Hell. Your souls shall merge with their Avatars. All that is in their destructive nature and power shall now be yours. 

Go forth and cover the landscape in blood. Destroy all that you see before you. Make them loose their faith and their path. Then when there is nothing left, nothing to hope for and nothing left to believe in they will all turn to me! 

For know this my faithful servants, for it is the hidden truth from all mortals; it is believed that all souls that do not believe in the afterlife, worship no deity and believe in nothing cease to exist upon their demise. 

It is not so! Disbelief is the tool of the Lord of Lies. It is my tool. Those who believe in nothing when they die are reborn in the Ninth Pit of Hell regardless of alignment. Those are the truly damned as their souls are consumed by me for all eternity. 

Go forth. Make them believe in nothing and the universe shall belong to us. Once I have consumed enough souls we can remake this realm and all others in my image! The final battle must be fought in this realm." 

With those final words the serpent slithered through solid stone back into the underworld from whence it came. 

The lord of Darkness was true to his word soon the Avatars of the Lords of the Nine walked the lands. Their essence had merged with the leaders of the Cipher faction imbuing them with unspeakable power and the will to dominate all others. Asmodeus, Mephistopheles, Baalzebul, Levistus, Malagard, Belial, Mammon, Dispator and Bel were now the names by which Ciphers were known and they carried out their lord's dark purpose for more then 100 mortal years. 


THE BLOOD WAR 

66 years after his first visit to Loftenwood the ETERNAL SERPENT once again visited his minions and again the lands shuddered under its ponderous weight. The Lords of the Nine gathered in the Shattered Temple deep within the Cipher homeland to listen to their lord and master: 

"A battle between Law and Chaos, the BLOOD WAR, has been raging for millennia between Devils and Demons. Millions have been slain on both sides in this eternal conflict. The organized minions of Hell battle the infinite Hordes of the Abyss. No side has emerged victorious in this conflict. This war will determine the face of evil for all time. It suits my purpose that this war be brought to Loftenwood and its surrounding lands. The time has come for mortals to be embroiled in this conflict. 

Go forth and defeat the faction known as the Dark Legion and all other forces that strive to pervert pure and natural evil from its natural form of Law into its aberrant chaotic form. Whether they know it or not they are agents of the Demonic Hordes of the Abyss. They cannot be allowed to prevail! 

To this end I will grant you even more power then previously. The DARK EIGHT generals of the BLOOD WAR shall now walk amongst you and lend their strength and appetite for destruction to your own. Each is a Pit Fiend of terrible power that controls a different aspect of the BLOOD WAR. May Furcas, Baalzephom, Zimimar, Zapan, Zaebos, Corin, Dagos and Paerza my eight most powerful pit fiend generals lead you to victory!" 

The serpent once again slithered to the deepest pit to watch the bloodshed above for all eternity, and the lands of Loftenwood were made brighter by his absence. 


RULES AND REGULATIONS 

Before the ETERNAL SERPENT departed he had these final bits of wisdom to govern the actions of the CIPHER faction. 

1. Cipher is a Lawful Evil Faction. It shall consist of one general, 4 commanders and 4 captains per the rules and regulations of Dungeon Eternal. Each of their essences shall be merged with one of the Lords of the Nine. 

2. As a Lawful Evil faction all members shall obey the rules and regulations of Dungeon Eternal or they will be subject to strict reprimand both by the leaders of the faction and the Dms of DEX (this goes without saying). 

3. Cipher may enter alliances with a faction which suits their current needs. Caution however is in order when making a deal with the Devil! 

4. Cipher is a full PK and PP faction. Everyone is KOS (kill on sight) and Pick Pocket targets with the following exceptions: 

A. Other members of Cipher who have the <C> designation. 
B. All Ciphers in training with the title Blackwood. 
C. All those who have a current alliance with Cipher. 
D. All those who are in a Cipher party. 

5. Entry into Cipher is complicated and arduous. Hell does not choose its champions lightly (If you are interested in joining contact a captain or commander). 

A. Any potential recruit must first find a SPONSOR. Only a general, commander or captain can sponsor a hopeful member. The sponsor is responsible for the actions and advancement of the recruit therefore they will carefully choose who they will sponsor. 
B. The sponsored recruit can then make a Blackwood character and must list in that character biography who his sponsor is for easy identification. 
C. A recruit must advance at least one Blackwood character to level 40 and must adventure fight, and Pk along side the Ciphers for a real life period of at least one continuous month. Trainees are advised to spend the month getting to know the members of Cipher. 
D. After a month's time has passed the Cipher members will vote on a trainee's membership. They will either be told they are suitable or unsuitable to join the champions of HELL. 

6. Know the difference between role playing and flaming. Role Playing is encouraged. Use the background information above. Flaming both on the forums and in shout channel is not acceptable and frankly beneath the dignity of a champion of Hell. Role playing will help you become a Cipher while flaming will not help you become or stay a Cipher. Have the wisdom to know the difference between the two! 

7. Ciphers may not party with any faction they are officially at war with beyond level 15 (Currently this includes only Sole and Order).

Mephistopheles once engineered his own coup, when he was replaced by Baron Molikroth. However, Molikroth was secretly Mephistopheles, and that duplicity has now ended (as have the lives of "Molikroth's" co-conspirators. The Lord of the Eighth appears as a 9-foot-tall humanoid with hell-red skin, horns, wings. He grips a magic ranseur that burns eternally. He prefers to drape himself in dramatic capes as black as the deepest void. Like the other archdukes of the Nine Hells, Mephistopheles failed to unseat Asmodeus's rulership over the Nine Hells. And like many other archdukes, he retained his position when the Reckoning was over. His biggest rival is Baalzebul, and his court is thick with plots against the Lord of the Flies.
Archduke Mephistopheles of Cannia, Lord of the Eighth

Asmodeus is at the very least an archdevil, but he could possess the power of a true deity. He resides in Malsheem but is rarely seen. Only when the elite of the Nine Hells gather in anyone of a hundred audience chambers does Asmodeus make his presence known, usually in the form of an unprepossessing humanoid with black hair, a black goatee, and eyes of flame. Asmodeus has been challenged many times, most recently during the Hells-wide rebellion called the Reckoning, but he has never been defeated.
Asmodeus Archfiend Ruler of Hell, Lord of the Ninth

The Hag Countess is not an archdevil but a supremely powerful night hag from Hades. Moloch once ruled this layer, but was cast down when he defied Asmodeus during the general rebellion that ripped through the Nine Hells some time past. Most authorities acknowledge that the Hag, one of Moloch's most trusted advisors, counseled Moloch to rebel. Of course, the rebellion failed, and during the Reckoning the Hag was set in Moloch's place. Moloch fled, and wherever he is hiding, it is certain that this archdevil bears a terrible grudge. The Hag Countess's stronghold is the core of a mountainsized boulder that perpetually rolls down Malbolge's slopes, though none of her nobles know exactly where it is or on what path it rolls. Instead, they host her when she occasionally visits them in their copper fortresses, assuming they can pierce her expert disguises.
Malagard Hag Countess, Lord of the Sixth

No one knows what Levistus looks like, because the prince is frozen deep within an iceberg. From the exterior, the prince looks like a great dark clot blearily realized through the ice. Asmodeus originally imprisoned Levistus in ice for a past betrayal. Though he allows the prince control over Phlegethos via mental contact with other devils, Asmodeus will not free Levistus. Despite his imprisonment, the plots of Levistus run deep. Should Levistus break free, his vengeance on the other lords of the Nine Hells, especially Asmodeus, would undoubtedly follow.
Prince Levistus of Stygia, Lord of the Fifth

Once, Baalzebul was an archon of Celestia called Triel, but he was cast down into the Nine Hells. Asmodeus quickly promoted Triel to devilhood in a dread ritual. Baalzebul's relentless drive for perfection served him well as climbed the ranks of devilry, culminating in Baalzebul's ascension to the lord of the Seventh. And Baalzebul didn't just attain his lordship--he deposed the earlier lord and expunged all mention of that entity. Leaving behind his former name with his former allegiance, Baalzebul is also called the Lord of Flies because not even a fly can escape his net of intrigues. Like virtually every other lord, Baalzebul once plotted against Asmodeus during the failed rebellion and purge known as the Reckoning. To punish Baalzebul, Asmodeus transformed his formerly angelic body into a melted, sluglike form. Now, Baalzebul openly plots against only Mephistopheles, Lord of the Eighth. But his undying anger yet burns for Asmodeus, as does his undying ambition for the throne of the King of the Nine Hells.
Archduke Baalzebul of Maladomini, Lord of the Sevenith

Mammon is an archdevil and so possesses almost deity-level power. In form, he resembles a 30-foot-long serpent with a human torso, head, and arms. He wields a harpoon-like spear, though its magic is the least of Mammon's impressive abilities. He rules from the center of the city of Minauros, inhabiting a mausoleum like structure of similarly massive proportions. Mammon is a turncoat's turncoat. Though he once allied with Dispater and Mephistopheles against Asmodeus, he was the first to abase himself before the Lord of the Ninth when Asmodeus finally proved victorious at the close of a failed rebellion called the Reckoning. Few of the other Lords would ever trust Mammon again, making him least likely to be involved in the next internal revolt.
Viscount Mammon of Minauros, Lord of the Third

The center of the Bronze Citadel holds the personal fortress of Bel, a pit fiend of great power who controls Avernus; in addition to being Lord of the First. Bel is also a general in the Blood War, though not one of the Dark Eight. Bel betrayed the former Lord of the First, Zariel, for his current position. It is whispered by his subordinates that Bel still keeps Zariel prisoner somewhere deep in the Bronze Citadel so that he can siphon her hellish power into himself, increasing his own abilities while slowly reducing her to just another soul shell. While Bel has succeeded where many failed before him, his climb to power seems to be stalled now, since he does not enjoy the support of other Lords of the Nine, except for possibly Asmodeus.
Bel the Pitfiend, Warlord of Aernus, Lord of the First

.Unlike with Bel, it is difficult to class Dispater as a specific "type" of devil or recall his origin, other than to say he is an archdevil. Like the other Lords of the Nine, he is an elite devil whose powers are waxing, and even pit fiends fall before his onslaught. He usually appears as a humanoid of supernatural height, dark hair, tiny horns, and resplendent garb. He always holds his badge of office, a rod of singular power. Dispater never takes risks and rarely leaves his Iron Tower. Only Asmodeus's call brings him forth. In the politics of The Nine Hells, Dispater and Mephistopheles, Lord of the Eighth, are allies, usually scheming against Baalzebul, Lord of the Seventh.
Archduke Dispater of Dis, Lord of the Second

Belial and Fierna are archdevils who take the form of slightly devilish-looking humanoids. Fierna fights with a blade of fire she summons at will, and Belial battles with a powerful ranseur. Fierna is Belial's daughter; he lets her wear the mantle of leadership in public, but really the two rule the layer of Phlegethos together
Great Belial of Phlegethos, Lord of the Fourth
